
[1]sadness

   SAD'NESS, n.

   1. Sorrowfulness; mournfulness; dejection of mind; as grief and sadness
   at the memory of sin.

   2. A melancholy look; gloom of countenance.

   Dim sadness did not spare Celestial visages.

   3. Seriousness; sedate gravity. Let every thing in a mournful subject
   have an air of sadness.
